.TH SEQ(1),User Commands,SEQ(1)

.SH NAME
seq - print sequences of numbers

.SH SYNOPSIS
seq [-w] [-f format] [-s string] [first [incr]] last

.SH DESCRIPTION
The seq utility prints a sequence of numbers, one per line (by default), from first (default 1) to last, in steps of incr (default 1). If first is larger than last, the default incr is -1.

.SH OPTIONS
-f format: Use a printf-style format string to print each number. The format must contain exactly one integer conversion (d, i, u, o, x, or X), optionally with an l length modifier. Default is %ld.

-s string: Use string as the separator between numbers. Default is a newline.

-w: Equalize the width of all numbers by padding with leading zeros or spaces.

.SH EXIT STATUS
The seq utility exits 0 on success, and >0 if an error occurs.

.SH EXAMPLES
Print 1 to 5:

$ seq 5

Print 0 to 10 in steps of 2:

$ seq 0 2 10

Print 1 to 3 with a comma separator:

$ seq -s , 3
